22 September 2014The Inter-Ministerial Task Team on the Nigeria tragedy led by Minister Jeff Radebe will be receiving the patients that were injured during the collapse of a building at the Synagogue Church of All Nations in Lagos, Nigeria.Members of the media are invited as follows: Date: 22 September 2014Time: Media to have access to the base from: 09h00Arrival of the flight: 10h00Venue: Air Force Base Swartkop (Pretoria)NB: We appeal to the media to protect the privacy of the patients.RSVP: Themba Thobela (Pretoria) Cell: 076 09 56 555 E-mail: Themba@gcis.gov.zaEnquiries: Phumla Williams Acting GCIS CEO Cell: 083 501 0139Issued by Government Communication (GCIS) on behalf of The Inter- Ministerial Task Team on the Nigeria tragedy 